.TH "ZIP_FTELL" "3" "December 18, 2017" "NiH" "Library Functions Manual"
.nh
.if n .ad l
.SH "NAME"
\fBzip_ftell\fR
\- tell position in file
.SH "LIBRARY"
libzip (-lzip)
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fB#include <zip.h>\fR
.sp
\fIzip_int64_t\fR
.PD 0
.HP 4n
\fBzip_ftell\fR(\fIzip_file_t\ *file\fR);
.PD
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The
\fBzip_ftell\fR()
function reports the current offset in the file.
.PP
\fBzip_ftell\fR
only works on uncompressed (stored) data.
When called on compressed data it will return an error.
.SH "RETURN VALUES"
If successful,
\fBzip_ftell\fR
returns the current file position.
Otherwise, \-1 is returned.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
libzip(3),
zip_fclose(3),
zip_fopen(3),
zip_fread(3),
zip_fseek(3)
.SH "HISTORY"
\fBzip_ftell\fR()
was added in libzip 1.2.0.
